<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-01-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="750" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d750">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/509.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-01-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 18, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>While recognizing equity Liberia’s proposal it is thought that
                            commissioners of five nations might tend to inject political questions.
                            Smaller commission might avoid complications attended with larger number
                            and Department therefore inclined to favor German suggestion
                            particularly if third commissioner should be an American, which would
                            probably be the case.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>